# Exercises: Mine Monero in the Web Browser with Coinhive JS Miner

In this exercise you will learn how to mine **Monero** using **Coinhive`s JavaScript Miner**. This miner can be integrated on web site. Miner use CPU to mine Monero. Monero is a **Proof of Work** cryptocurrency that can be mine with computational power from a **CPU** or **GPU**. It uses the **CryptoNight hashing algorithm**. There are currently no ASICs for Monero, which means that anyone with a computer can mine it.

1. 1.Create Monero Account

1. First you need monero wallet. Go to [https://mymonero.com/#/](https://mymonero.com/#/) and **Create an account**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Write down your **private key** and go further.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Then write down your **address** and click **receive**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Here write down your **Payment ID** and click **receive**

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. 2.Setup the Miner

1. First you must register on Coinhive.com.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. After registration go to Settings. Here you must take your **Site Key (public)** and setup **payments.** First click on **Sites &amp; API Keys**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. From **Sites &amp; API Keys** you can copy your **Site Key.**

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Then go to **Payment Settings** and put your Monero Payment Address which you received from Monero wallet. Here also you can setup the amount of minimum payout. Mention that amount of 0.5 XMR and more is tax free, but for smaller amounts you must pay transaction fees.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Let`s create a simple web site contains the mining script.

| \&lt;!DOCTYPE html\&gt;\&lt;html\&gt;\&lt;head\&gt;\&lt;script src=&quot;https://authedmine.com/lib/authedmine.min.js&quot;\&gt;\&lt;/script\&gt;\&lt;script\&gt; var miner = new CoinHive.Anonymous(&#39;YOUR SITE KEY&#39;, {throttle: 0.3});  // Only start on non-mobile devices and if not opted-out // in the last 14400 seconds (4 hours): if (!miner.isMobile() &amp;&amp; !miner.didOptOut(14400)) {  miner.start(); }\&lt;/script\&gt;\&lt;/head\&gt;\&lt;body\&gt; \&lt;h1\&gt;Mine for me.\&lt;/h1\&gt;\&lt;/body\&gt;\&lt;/html\&gt; |
| --- |

Note that the Miner is loaded from a different domain (authedmine.com) that enforces an opt-in as soon as miner.start() is called.

**throttle** : Set the fraction of time that threads should be idle. A value of 0 means no throttling (i.e. full speed), a value of 0.5 means that threads will stay idle 50% of the time, with 0.8 they will stay idle 80% of the time. In our case 0.3 means stay idle 30% of the time so CPU mining usage is near 70%.

1. When you open the site the miner will open message window and start mining.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Press **ctrl** + **alt** + **del** , open **Task Manager** -\&gt; **Performance** and look on your CPU. CPU load has increased significantly because you are already mining monero.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Now if open the Dashboard you can see your mining statistics.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)
